<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="altogether-adv">altogether <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌɔːltə'ɡeðə(r)/    美 /ˌɔːltə'ɡeðər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-in-all-in-total">1.★ <strong>总共；一共(in all / in total)</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There are altogether eleven books on the shelf, of which five are mine. 
书架上总共有11本书，其中5本是我的。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-all-in-all">2.★ <strong>总的说来 (all in all)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The food was good and we loved the atmosphere and the people. Altogether it was a great evening.
吃的东西不错，而且我们喜欢那里的气氛和人。总之，那天晚上过得很愉快。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>完全地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The train went slower and slower until it stopped altogether.
火车速度越来越慢，最后彻底停了下来。</p></div></div>